Protestor: ♪ Southern trees
bear strange fruit ♪

00:09.493 --> 00:14.513
♪ Blood on the leaves
and blood at the root ♪

00:14.590 --> 00:22.170
♪ Black bodies swinging
in the Southern breeze ♪

00:22.248 --> 00:25.674
♪ Strange fruit hanging ♪

00:25.752 --> 00:30.029
♪ From the poplar trees ♪

00:30.106 --> 00:36.685
♪ Here is a fruit
for the crows to pluck ♪

00:36.763 --> 00:40.447
♪ For the rain to gather ♪

00:40.524 --> 00:44.618
♪ For the wind to suck ♪

00:44.695 --> 00:48.939
♪ For the sun to rot ♪

00:48.941 --> 00:56.872
♪ For the tree to drop ♪

00:56.949 --> 01:03.712
♪ Here is a strange
and a bitter ♪

01:03.790 --> 01:12.797
♪ Crop ♪

01:12.799 --> 01:15.149
♪

01:15.225 --> 01:16.483
Zoey:
<i>  If you don't look too closely,</i>

01:16.560 --> 01:20.913
<i>  you might think</i>
<i>  this is a scene from 1968.</i>

01:20.990 --> 01:23.157
<i>  But it's not.</i>

01:23.233 --> 01:25.918
<i>  Actually, it's</i>
<i>  more than 50 years later,</i>

01:25.995 --> 01:27.328
<i>  and we were still</i>
<i>  fighting against</i>

01:27.404 --> 01:31.406
<i>  the racial injustice</i>
<i>  and rampant inequality</i>

01:31.484 --> 01:34.093
<i>  that continued</i>
<i>  to plague our country.</i>

01:34.170 --> 01:39.748
<i>  Why? Because our nation</i>
<i>  wasn't looking close enough.</i>

01:39.826 --> 01:40.266
Protestors:
[ Chanting ] Say their names!

01:40.343 --> 01:42.250
Say their names!

01:42.328 --> 01:43.994
Say their names!

01:43.996 --> 01:45.179
Say their names!

01:45.255 --> 01:47.998
Say their names!

01:48.000 --> 01:49.516
Say their names!
[ Cellphones vibrating,
alert whining ]

01:49.593 --> 01:52.594
[ Fading ] Say their names!
Say their names!

01:52.672 --> 01:54.429
[ Cellphones vibrating,
alert whining ]

01:54.507 --> 01:56.006
Campus Policeman:
[ Over loudspeaker ]
The County of Los Angeles

01:56.008 --> 02:01.436
has issued a curfew,
which includes this campus.

02:01.514 --> 02:04.957
Students must evacuate
the premises now.

02:05.034 --> 02:09.370
Gather your belongings
and disperse immediately.

02:09.446 --> 02:11.856
This is your final warning.

02:11.858 --> 02:13.281
<i>  In fact, for decades,</i>

02:13.359 --> 02:17.711
<i>  not only was the nation</i>
<i>  not looking closely enough,</i>

02:17.788 --> 02:20.714
<i>  but people actively</i>
<i>  turned a blind eye,</i>

02:20.791 --> 02:24.218
<i>  and that blind eye turned</i>
<i>  into a national blind spot,</i>

02:24.294 --> 02:26.203
<i>  until eventually,</i>

02:26.205 --> 02:27.388
<i>  there was</i>
<i>  nowhere else to look</i>

02:27.464 --> 02:31.542
<i>  but directly at it.</i>

02:31.544 --> 02:34.469
♪ Watch out, world,
I'm grown now ♪

02:34.547 --> 02:36.881
♪ I'm grown ♪

02:36.883 --> 02:39.158
♪ Learn something new
every day ♪

02:39.235 --> 02:41.886
♪ I don't know,
so I'mma feel my way ♪

02:41.888 --> 02:43.812
♪ Got the weight of the world
on me ♪

02:43.890 --> 02:47.500
♪ But no regrets,
this is what I say ♪

02:47.576 --> 02:51.078
♪ Watch out, world,
I'm grown now ♪

02:51.155 --> 02:51.987
♪ I'm grown ♪
♪ You can tell me ♪

02:52.064 --> 02:58.068
♪ My heart beating so loud ♪

02:58.070 --> 03:01.405
♪ Mama, look, I'm grown now ♪

03:01.407 --> 03:05.667
♪ I'm grown ♪

03:05.745 --> 03:07.094
Protestors:
[ Chanting ] Justice for Marcus!

03:07.171 --> 03:08.412
Justice for Marcus!

03:08.414 --> 03:10.931
Justice for Marcus!

03:11.008 --> 03:12.266
Yo [bleep] the curfew, man.
It's ridiculous.

03:12.342 --> 03:15.436
How are they gonna give us
15 minutes to clear out?

03:15.512 --> 03:16.587
Aaron: This is a tactic
the government uses

03:16.589 --> 03:18.030
when shit gets
uncomfortable for them.

03:18.107 --> 03:19.590
Mm-hmm.
I'm not leaving.

03:19.592 --> 03:22.443
Yo, I mean, this is the time
we push the boundaries, guys.

03:22.519 --> 03:23.944
I say we all go downtown
where it's really active.

03:24.021 --> 03:28.432
Uh, well, I for one feel like
we came, we saw, we conquered.

03:28.434 --> 03:31.769
And I feel like we should
probably eat now?

03:31.771 --> 03:32.878
Is anyone else starving?
I am.

03:32.955 --> 03:34.380
Doug: No.
Stay safe out there, kids.

03:34.457 --> 03:38.609
Alright, well, I love you guys.
Las Vidas Negras Importan!

03:38.611 --> 03:40.869
Yeah, guys. I think I'm gonna
head back to the house, too.

03:40.947 --> 03:42.037
I'm -- You know, normally,
I'm so down

03:42.114 --> 03:43.614
to get arrested
for the cause,

03:43.616 --> 03:46.708
but if I do get arrested now,
then who's gonna feed Luna?

03:46.786 --> 03:47.893
Yeah. Me, too.
Like, a part of me

03:47.970 --> 03:49.303
wants to go downtown,
but the other part of me

03:49.379 --> 03:53.307
doesn't want to mess
with those rubber bullets, so...

03:53.383 --> 03:54.792
Look, I get if you want
to come with us,

03:54.794 --> 03:56.902
but I gotta warn you,
it's gonna get a little crazy.

03:56.979 --> 03:58.737
Oh. Yeah, no.
I'm not going with you.

03:58.814 --> 04:00.388
I know my strengths,
and staying out past

04:00.466 --> 04:01.574
a government-enforced
curfew --

04:01.650 --> 04:03.968
unfortunately,
not one of them.

04:03.970 --> 04:05.319
But please stay safe.
Yeah.

04:05.395 --> 04:07.413
Like, for real. Okay.

04:07.490 --> 04:08.730
-Bye, guys.
-Later.

04:08.808 --> 04:09.748
Dude, can you please
go with them?

04:09.825 --> 04:12.251
It'll really mess with
my frontal lobe

04:12.328 --> 04:13.586
if I have to worry
about the both of us.

04:13.662 --> 04:15.813
Yeah, no. Uh,
I'm not going with them.

04:15.815 --> 04:17.239
I'm going downtown.

04:17.316 --> 04:19.650
You know, some of us actually
care about what's happening.

04:19.652 --> 04:21.001
Okay.
Doug: Bro, it's all good.

04:21.078 --> 04:23.504
There's four of us. We can
all keep an eye on each other.

04:23.580 --> 04:24.913
Yeah, and if it makes you
more comfortable, we can,

04:24.991 --> 04:26.173
like, pick a spot to meet up
if anybody gets lost.

04:26.250 --> 04:28.583
Word.
Whatever, man.

04:28.661 --> 04:29.159
Alright, let's go
get the car.

04:29.161 --> 04:30.844
Okay.

04:30.921 --> 04:33.347
♪

04:33.423 --> 04:38.185
So, uh, we're keeping an eye
out for each other now?

04:38.262 --> 04:39.427
Um, I was just trying
to keep an eye on you.

04:39.505 --> 04:42.339
[ Chuckles ]

04:42.341 --> 04:43.507
What is the one?
[ Indistinct Spanish ]

04:43.509 --> 04:45.767
[ Laughs ]
Stop!

04:45.845 --> 04:46.619
Oh, you should definitely
try the lengua.

04:46.695 --> 04:48.362
It's so good.
Hard pass.

04:48.438 --> 04:49.771
The only lengua I want
in my mouth is yours.

04:49.849 --> 04:52.625
It better be the only lengua
you have in your mouth.

04:52.701 --> 04:54.184
[ Police radio chatter ]

04:54.186 --> 04:56.870
Thank you for your service,
guys. Appreciate you.

04:56.947 --> 04:58.797
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:58.874 --> 05:04.528
♪

05:04.530 --> 05:08.641
[ Sighing ] Ooh. Damn.
It is really crazy out there.

05:08.717 --> 05:10.217
I'm kind of glad we didn't go
downtown with the rest of them.

05:10.294 --> 05:11.218
Mm-hmm.
So, I'm in a thread

05:11.295 --> 05:12.553
with some friends, right?
Uh-huh.

05:12.629 --> 05:15.055
And they just said
the Beverly Center just got hit.

05:15.132 --> 05:16.723
Nomi:
Why do they even do that?

05:16.800 --> 05:17.724
I mean, we didn't hit anything
at the Women's March.

05:17.801 --> 05:19.209
Remember?
It was so peaceful.

05:19.211 --> 05:22.470
Well, we also pregamed
with mimosas and Eggs Benedict

05:22.548 --> 05:23.489
and wore pink, fuzzy hats.

05:23.566 --> 05:25.566
I'd have to say
it's a tad different.

05:25.642 --> 05:27.142
No, I know.
I'm just saying

05:27.219 --> 05:29.053
that burning
and looting people's stores

05:29.055 --> 05:31.313
should definitely not
be a part of this.

05:31.390 --> 05:32.831
Oh, but you're fine
with the flowery chanting,

05:32.908 --> 05:34.816
the bedazzled signage,

05:34.894 --> 05:35.650
and the big,
buttery smooth Black man

05:35.728 --> 05:38.153
singing "Strange Fruit"?

05:38.230 --> 05:42.066
But when stuff gets real,
you're off the cause?

05:42.068 --> 05:44.068
No, I'm absolutely
<i>  on</i>  the cause, Jaz.

05:44.070 --> 05:45.919
I just don't understand
why those people think

05:45.996 --> 05:49.164
that looting
is the answer.

05:49.241 --> 05:51.350
Those people?
Those people?

05:51.427 --> 05:52.242
[ Crowd shouting indistinctly ]

05:52.244 --> 05:55.596
[ Siren wailing ]

05:55.672 --> 05:58.432
[ Donny Hathaway's
"Little Ghetto Boy" plays ]

05:58.508 --> 06:00.359
♪

06:00.436 --> 06:06.198
♪ Little ghetto boy ♪

06:06.275 --> 06:08.200
♪ Playing in the ghetto street ♪

06:08.277 --> 06:10.094
Policeman: [ Over loudspeaker ]
This is a civil disturbance,

06:10.096 --> 06:12.020
and curfew is now in effect.

06:12.098 --> 06:14.022
Leave the area immediately,

06:14.100 --> 06:15.933
or you'll be subject
to the use of force,

06:15.935 --> 06:17.710
including
crowd control munitions.

06:17.786 --> 06:19.937
We are peacefully
assembling

06:19.939 --> 06:20.938
and have every right
to continue to do so!

06:20.940 --> 06:22.289
Exactly!
This is a violation!

06:25.035 --> 06:26.460
Look, we pay you
to protect us.

06:26.536 --> 06:29.630
All we're doing is exercising
our constitutional rights!

06:29.706 --> 06:30.839
Oh, my God!

06:33.135 --> 06:34.393
Come on!

06:34.470 --> 06:40.958
♪

06:40.960 --> 06:42.309
[ Protestors coughing ]

06:42.386 --> 06:44.903
♪

06:44.980 --> 06:49.557
♪ Little ghetto boy ♪

06:49.635 --> 06:56.582
♪ Playing in the ghetto street ♪

06:56.659 --> 06:59.993
♪ Whatcha gonna do
when you grow up ♪

07:00.070 --> 07:05.424
♪ And have to face
responsibility? ♪

07:05.501 --> 07:07.985
[ Siren wails in distance ]
Nomi: Okay, I'm not so worried

07:07.987 --> 07:08.743
about the destruction
of property...

07:08.821 --> 07:10.003
Okay.
...but come on.

07:10.080 --> 07:11.505
The looting and burning
of people's businesses

07:11.581 --> 07:13.840
is not gonna help
hold racist cops accountable.

07:13.917 --> 07:17.770
Of course it's not gonna
help hold them accountable,

07:17.846 --> 07:20.088
because nothing
holds them accountable.

07:20.166 --> 07:21.756
That's exactly
why this is happening.

07:21.834 --> 07:23.609
It's -- It's the last resort

07:23.686 --> 07:26.261
for people who have just
been ignored for too long.

07:26.338 --> 07:31.508
Martin even said that riots
are the language of the unheard.

07:31.510 --> 07:33.601
Okay, Coretta.

07:33.679 --> 07:34.602
Looks like Aaron's
been serving you the "D"

07:34.680 --> 07:35.621
<i>  and</i>  that knowledge.

07:35.698 --> 07:36.955
Alright, look.
I obviously understand

07:37.032 --> 07:40.033
that human life
is more valuable than property.

07:40.110 --> 07:42.110
I just -- I don't know.

07:42.188 --> 07:44.021
I feel sorry
for the small business owners

07:44.023 --> 07:45.372
who built their livelihoods
from nothing,

07:45.449 --> 07:49.117
and now some opportunists
are using this man's death

07:49.195 --> 07:51.028
as an excuse
to destroy that.

07:51.030 --> 07:55.048
Okay. My dad built
one of those small businesses,

07:55.125 --> 07:57.810
but when it comes
to saving Black lives,

07:57.886 --> 07:59.144
best believe
Kermit wouldn't mind

07:59.221 --> 08:01.705
getting his food truck
destroyed.

08:01.707 --> 08:03.298
So if something needs
to get burned down

08:03.375 --> 08:05.892
or get looted
to shake things up,

08:05.969 --> 08:07.302
then so be it.
I-I don't know.

08:07.379 --> 08:09.804
I'm just baffled. So --
So you guys are cool, then,

08:09.882 --> 08:12.883
with the looting and rioting?
Not<i>  cool</i>  with it,

08:12.885 --> 08:15.327
but you choosing to focus on
the looting and rioting

08:15.404 --> 08:19.723
is a part of a longstanding
history of racist thinking.

08:19.725 --> 08:22.668
Hold on, Zoey.
"R-Racist thinking"?

08:22.745 --> 08:24.911
So -- So you're
calling me a racist?

08:24.988 --> 08:26.988
Are -- Are you kidding me?

08:33.572 --> 08:36.164
Okay. I can't believe
you think I'm racist.

08:36.242 --> 08:37.332
Girl, calm down.
Nobody said that.

08:37.409 --> 08:38.517
Right.
Actually, Zoey kinda did.

08:38.594 --> 08:41.836
Okay, I said you had
some racist thinking,

08:41.914 --> 08:44.005
not "Nomi hates
Black people."

08:44.083 --> 08:45.173
Oh, my God.
Right, okay.

08:45.251 --> 08:46.692
So my thinking
is racist,

08:46.769 --> 08:48.769
which mean
I think racist things

08:48.845 --> 08:50.178
about people
based on their skin color,

08:50.256 --> 08:54.015
which is literally the
definition of being a racist.

08:54.093 --> 08:54.941
That's who you think I am?

08:55.018 --> 08:58.111
Again, no.
We know who you are.

08:58.188 --> 09:00.447
But choosing to criticize

09:00.524 --> 09:03.116
the way oppressed people
are reacting to their oppression

09:03.193 --> 09:06.211
versus criticizing
the oppression itself

09:06.288 --> 09:07.271
is a part of the problem.

09:07.273 --> 09:10.549
[ Clapping ]
Mm. Wow. [ Laughs ]

09:10.626 --> 09:12.959
I need to get Aaron
a thank-you basket.

09:13.036 --> 09:14.461
Just six months ago,
you confused Clarence Thomas

09:14.538 --> 09:15.387
with Danny Glover.

09:15.464 --> 09:16.797
Girl, look at you now.

09:16.873 --> 09:20.708
I still think Clarence could
play Danny in a biopic.

09:20.786 --> 09:22.286
Look, Nomi. In the past,

09:22.288 --> 09:24.879
whenever you felt like any of us
had problematic thinking,

09:24.957 --> 09:26.473
you called us on it,

09:26.550 --> 09:27.715
and we weren't pressed.
That part.

09:27.793 --> 09:30.794
Yeah, that's because
when I called you on it,

09:30.796 --> 09:31.812
I didn't use
inflammatory language

09:31.888 --> 09:34.072
or personally attack
your character.

09:34.149 --> 09:35.723
[ Cellphone chimes ]
I just got another text.

09:35.801 --> 09:39.136
Looks like they're about to hit
the Barnes & Noble at The Grove.

09:39.138 --> 09:40.895
Anybody want
that new Zane?

09:40.973 --> 09:41.805
[ Clicks tongue ]

09:41.807 --> 09:44.141
♪

09:44.143 --> 09:46.326
Aaron: That shit was crazy.
Doug: Dawg.

09:46.403 --> 09:49.237
Where they at?
I don't know.
We told them to meet us here.

09:49.315 --> 09:50.572
Where's Kiela?
What? I don't know.

09:50.649 --> 09:53.483
We thought she was with you.
No, man. She ran off.

09:53.485 --> 09:55.093
I can't find her anywhere.
Ah. Man.

09:55.170 --> 09:56.336
Can I use your phone?
Mine's dead.

09:56.413 --> 09:58.580
Yeah, here.
This is crazy, man.

09:58.657 --> 10:00.432
Bad service.

10:00.509 --> 10:01.266
Gonna text her.
Alright.

10:03.162 --> 10:08.607
♪

10:08.684 --> 10:10.500
Bro, are you
smashing my sister?

10:10.502 --> 10:11.610
Whoa!

10:11.687 --> 10:13.928
No. I mean --

10:14.006 --> 10:16.673
Hey, Kiela?

10:16.675 --> 10:18.342
Kiela?

10:18.344 --> 10:19.401
Kiki!

10:21.013 --> 10:23.530
Hey, um...

10:23.607 --> 10:25.031
back at the taco stand,
did you --

10:25.108 --> 10:29.019
did you not see those Black
protesters standing right there

10:29.021 --> 10:31.538
when you thanked the cops?

10:31.615 --> 10:35.617
[ Sighs ]

10:35.694 --> 10:37.302
Kind of odd you're calling them
Black protesters

10:37.379 --> 10:38.637
and not just protesters.

10:38.714 --> 10:42.641
I only say that because
it felt a little insensitive

10:42.718 --> 10:45.202
for you to make that comment
in front of them.

10:45.204 --> 10:47.312
I mean, come on.
Thanking the very people

10:47.389 --> 10:49.665
that they were
protesting against today?

10:49.741 --> 10:51.558
It felt -- I don't know.
I-I-It felt kind of gross.

10:51.635 --> 10:53.727
Gross?

10:53.803 --> 10:55.061
It's gross to thank my uncle
or your cousin

10:55.138 --> 10:56.730
or our family members
that are in the military?

10:56.806 --> 10:58.973
[ Sighs ]

10:59.051 --> 11:00.066
Got to be honest,
feels a little grosser

11:00.143 --> 11:01.476
that you're trying
to vilify all of them.

11:01.553 --> 11:05.146
[ Scoffs ] Okay, I'm just
saying that, in this moment,

11:05.224 --> 11:07.833
it felt like a blatant disregard
for those people

11:07.910 --> 11:09.726
who are in direct conflict
with the cops.

11:09.728 --> 11:13.005
I mean, had you done that
in front of my friends --

11:13.081 --> 11:17.567
Ana.
It was a thank you, okay?

11:17.569 --> 11:18.326
Please do not try to turn this
into an argument

11:18.404 --> 11:20.404
and make me the bad guy.

11:20.406 --> 11:23.665
We all know the real bad guys
were the Black protesters.

11:23.742 --> 11:26.501
♪

11:26.578 --> 11:28.745
I'm kidding.

11:28.747 --> 11:30.263
♪

11:33.268 --> 11:34.751
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

11:34.753 --> 11:37.421
Hold on, hold up.
Bro, bro, bro.

11:37.423 --> 11:38.697
Yo, can we talk
about these texts

11:38.774 --> 11:40.866
so we can get
this energy right, man?

11:40.943 --> 11:42.350
Bro, we're --
we're gonna find Kiela.

11:42.428 --> 11:45.779
I need you to know, nothing
serious happened between us.

11:45.855 --> 11:46.947
We kissed, and that's it.

11:47.023 --> 11:49.099
Think I care about that
right now?

11:49.101 --> 11:50.542
You obviously don't care
about loyalty.

11:50.619 --> 11:53.545
Thinking it's fine to desecrate
the temple of our friendship

11:53.622 --> 11:56.606
by fondling my kin?

11:56.608 --> 11:58.866
Hey, yo, even now,
you mad weird.

11:58.944 --> 12:00.627
[ Cellphone chimes ]

12:00.704 --> 12:02.036
Yo, it's Aaron.
He said he found her.

12:02.114 --> 12:03.371
Come on,
come on, come on.

12:03.449 --> 12:05.131
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:05.208 --> 12:10.637
♪

12:10.714 --> 12:14.066
Hey, we're about to order
some Thai. You want in?

12:14.142 --> 12:15.642
I mean, I don't really
<i>  like</i>  Thai,

12:15.719 --> 12:18.979
but if I say no,
then am I racist?

12:19.055 --> 12:21.298
Nomi, why are you being
so defensive about this?

12:21.300 --> 12:24.892
Yeah, you are seriously
on some White fragility shit.

12:24.970 --> 12:27.579
Wow. Suppose
you think that, too?

12:27.656 --> 12:29.639
Yeah. You're -- You're White,
and you're --

12:29.641 --> 12:30.916
you're always taking
those calcium chews, so...

12:30.993 --> 12:33.901
You have no idea
what that is, do you?
Mnh-mnh.

12:33.979 --> 12:35.069
Yeah, you know what?
It doesn't even matter,

12:35.147 --> 12:36.088
'cause I'm done with
this whole conversation.

12:36.164 --> 12:39.073
Hey, hold on.
Just so you know...
Hmm.

12:39.151 --> 12:41.743
...you "being done"
with this conversation

12:41.820 --> 12:44.078
instead of recognizing your
participation in the problem

12:44.156 --> 12:46.247
is the exact definition
of White fragility.

12:46.325 --> 12:47.248
Mm.
It's like you don't even want

12:47.326 --> 12:48.416
to have
the tough conversation.

12:48.494 --> 12:50.327
I was trying to have
the tough conversation,

12:50.329 --> 12:51.770
but my best friends
told me

12:51.847 --> 12:54.422
that I have, like, a huge blind
spot when it comes to race,

12:54.500 --> 12:55.832
and I'm --
I'm having a hard time

12:55.834 --> 12:58.168
wrapping my head around that.
Nomi, don't you think

12:58.170 --> 13:00.687
it's because you view the world
differently than we do?

13:00.764 --> 13:02.689
Mm-hmm.
Sometimes you can't help

13:02.766 --> 13:04.841
but perpetuate
what's ingrained in you.

13:04.843 --> 13:06.009
Zoey: Mm-hmm.
What's --

13:06.011 --> 13:08.345
What's ingrained in me?

13:08.347 --> 13:11.531
By which do you mean
how Jewish people just like me

13:11.608 --> 13:12.958
have historically marched
alongside Black people

13:13.035 --> 13:15.685
for civil rights
since Day One?

13:15.687 --> 13:19.280
Just like I marched
with you guys today?

13:19.358 --> 13:20.874
G-Guys, this is --
this is beyond crazy.

13:20.950 --> 13:23.951
Nomi, the only reason
we are calling you on this

13:24.029 --> 13:24.636
is because we love you.

13:24.713 --> 13:28.548
So much.

13:28.625 --> 13:30.550
[ Voice breaking ]
If I was with someone

13:30.627 --> 13:31.977
who I thought was homophobic
or anti-Semitic,

13:32.054 --> 13:35.630
I wouldn't be sitting here
trying to make them feel better.

13:35.707 --> 13:37.040
In fact, I wouldn't be
friends with them at all.

13:37.042 --> 13:38.542
So if you guys think
that I'm, like, racist

13:38.544 --> 13:39.876
or -- or problematic
or whatever,

13:39.878 --> 13:41.711
then why would you still
want to be friends with me?

13:41.713 --> 13:47.308
♪

13:51.056 --> 13:54.833
Nomi's Mom:<i>  Look, honey, it's</i>
<i>  a difficult time right now.</i>

13:54.910 --> 13:56.076
<i>  Everybody's emotions</i>
<i>  are high.</i>

13:56.152 --> 13:57.151
I know, but, Mom,
I can't believe

13:57.229 --> 13:58.562
my friends actually
think this of me.

13:58.564 --> 14:01.064
<i>  Yeah, but you know</i>
<i>  none of that stuff is true.</i>

14:01.066 --> 14:02.507
<i>  You're not a racist.</i>

14:02.584 --> 14:05.326
<i>  Your dad and I did not</i>
<i>  raise you to see color.</i>

14:05.404 --> 14:06.920
Okay, but, Mom, saying
that you don't see color

14:06.996 --> 14:09.014
is basically saying

14:09.091 --> 14:10.998
that you don't see someone
in their entirety,

14:11.076 --> 14:12.667
and that's actually
pretty problematic.

14:12.744 --> 14:14.594
<i>  Problematic?</i>

14:14.671 --> 14:16.003
<i>  N-Now you sound like</i>
<i>  your friends.</i>

14:16.081 --> 14:18.857
Oh, my God. Mom, you don't need
to get so defensive.

14:18.934 --> 14:20.433
<i>  No, I'm getting</i>
<i>  defensive because</i>

14:20.510 --> 14:21.676
<i>  you're challenging</i>
<i> </i> my<i>  character.</i>

14:21.753 --> 14:25.363
Your character?

14:25.440 --> 14:28.683
[ Whispering ]
About your character.

14:28.760 --> 14:29.926
[ Sirens wailing,
indistinct conversations ]

14:29.928 --> 14:39.953
♪

14:40.029 --> 14:40.937
[ Fire truck horn blaring ]

14:40.939 --> 14:43.440
What happened?

14:43.442 --> 14:45.050
She was
teargassed again.

14:45.127 --> 14:46.218
Oh, my God.
Are you okay?

14:46.294 --> 14:47.627
[ Kiela sniffles ]
Can you open your eyes?

14:47.704 --> 14:49.963
No.

14:50.039 --> 14:52.465
What can I do?
Nothing. Just --

14:52.542 --> 14:54.467
Just give me
a minute, please.

14:54.544 --> 14:56.302
There's got to be
something I can do to help.

14:56.379 --> 14:58.622
I just want to make sure
you're okay.

14:58.624 --> 15:01.048
No, I'm --
I'm<i>  not</i>  okay.

15:01.126 --> 15:02.642
I'm just -- I'm not.

15:02.719 --> 15:05.395
This is just all
so messed up.

15:07.891 --> 15:09.390
How does something like this
even happen?

15:09.468 --> 15:13.561
[ Crying ] You know, I-I'm here
protesting police brutality,

15:13.639 --> 15:14.913
and then I get brutalized
by the police?

15:14.990 --> 15:19.066
It just -- It just does--
It doesn't make sense.

15:19.144 --> 15:21.068
You know, I don't even know
what we did wrong.

15:21.146 --> 15:23.088
It's not your fault.

15:23.165 --> 15:26.908
You didn't do anything wrong.
[ Crying ]

15:26.985 --> 15:29.169
♪ I see them bloom ♪

15:29.245 --> 15:31.171
[ Sirens chirping, wailing ]

15:31.247 --> 15:34.491
♪ For me and you ♪

15:34.493 --> 15:37.160
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

15:37.162 --> 15:38.920
♪ And I think to myself ♪

15:38.997 --> 15:45.168
♪

15:45.170 --> 15:47.520
♪ What a wonderful world ♪

15:47.597 --> 15:50.674
♪

15:50.676 --> 15:53.601
♪ What a wonderful world ♪

15:53.679 --> 15:55.937
♪

15:56.014 --> 15:59.516
♪ What a wonderful world ♪

15:59.518 --> 16:02.627
♪

16:02.704 --> 16:04.111
[ Scoffs ]
This is so crazy.

16:04.189 --> 16:07.281
Mm.
Aaron just texted the group.

16:07.359 --> 16:08.708
Apparently, Luca's sister
got teargassed.

16:08.785 --> 16:10.210
Oh, shit.

16:10.286 --> 16:12.286
Still feel like thanking your
buddies back at the taco truck

16:12.364 --> 16:14.472
for their service?

16:14.549 --> 16:16.032
You're not still on this,
are you?

16:16.034 --> 16:16.883
No. No, not at all.

16:16.960 --> 16:18.310
Good.

16:18.386 --> 16:22.038
I'm just saying, it only
further reinforces my point

16:22.040 --> 16:23.982
of how right now is not the
ideal time to be thanking cops,

16:24.059 --> 16:25.967
that's all.

16:26.044 --> 16:28.211
Ana, I'm not going
to argue with you

16:28.213 --> 16:29.988
about something
we already put to bed.

16:30.065 --> 16:32.232
No, we actually
<i>  didn't</i>  put it to bed.

16:32.308 --> 16:33.992
You just made
some dumbass joke

16:34.069 --> 16:35.218
and then shut down
the conversation.

16:35.220 --> 16:36.720
Here we go.
"Here we go," what?

16:36.722 --> 16:40.332
You just -- just digging in,
just not letting anything go.

16:40.408 --> 16:43.001
The constant, like,
back and forth.

16:43.078 --> 16:45.003
I'm so sick of arguing with you
about nothing.

16:45.080 --> 16:48.656
Today was not nothing.

16:48.734 --> 16:50.658
This is something
that I care about.

16:50.736 --> 16:52.902
Really? 'Cause one day, you're
volunteering for D.A.R.E.,

16:52.904 --> 16:56.589
and then the next, you're
yelling at me for thanking cops.

16:56.666 --> 16:58.683
You don't know where you stand
on half these issues,

16:58.760 --> 16:59.851
and<i>  that's</i>  the problem.

16:59.928 --> 17:01.261
Okay, that is not fair.

17:01.337 --> 17:05.265
I am allowed to have nuanced
points of view, Javi.

17:05.341 --> 17:07.025
And it's okay
that they differ from yours.

17:07.102 --> 17:09.269
I don't only have to think and
act the way that you want me to.

17:09.345 --> 17:11.479
That's not what I'm saying.
Then what are you saying?

17:14.943 --> 17:15.867
I just don't think
a relationship

17:15.944 --> 17:16.776
should be this hard.

17:18.187 --> 17:21.873
♪

17:21.950 --> 17:23.950
Yeah, I don't think
I can do this anymore.

17:24.027 --> 17:27.545
♪

17:27.622 --> 17:28.863
Well, then, uh...

17:28.940 --> 17:31.608
♪

17:31.610 --> 17:34.201
I guess we finally both found
something that we agree on.

17:34.279 --> 17:40.892
♪

17:40.969 --> 17:41.709
[ Door opens ]

17:41.787 --> 17:49.809
♪

17:49.886 --> 17:52.570
Guys, it's okay. You don't need
to trail behind me anymore.

17:52.647 --> 17:57.317
It's -- It's fine, but, um,
thank you for having my back.

17:57.393 --> 17:58.484
I'll call you later, bro.
Night.

18:01.807 --> 18:02.897
Alright, y'all.
I'mma head out, too.

18:02.974 --> 18:04.641
But it's been amazing,
my Black brethren.

18:04.643 --> 18:05.917
Powerful night.
But I gotta go see Zoey.

18:05.994 --> 18:09.570
She keeps asking me
what, uh, White fragility means.

18:09.648 --> 18:10.146
Feel like she should
already know that, but...

18:10.148 --> 18:13.983
Later.

18:13.985 --> 18:16.820
Crazy night.
Yep.

18:16.822 --> 18:19.322
Look, bro...
my apologies.

18:19.324 --> 18:20.598
You know, I shouldn't have
crossed that line

18:20.675 --> 18:21.933
with your sister,
and moving forward,

18:22.010 --> 18:24.769
you're not gonna have to worry,
'cause I don't --

18:24.846 --> 18:27.105
I don't want to get in the
middle of siblings like that,

18:27.182 --> 18:31.000
or desecrate the...temple
of our friendship

18:31.002 --> 18:32.426
and fondle --

18:32.504 --> 18:33.928
My kin.
Right.

18:34.005 --> 18:37.023
[ Sighs ]

18:37.100 --> 18:38.283
Much appreciated.

18:38.360 --> 18:39.767
My man.

18:39.845 --> 18:42.528
Have a good night.
Stay safe.

18:42.605 --> 18:45.457
Jazz: Ooh.
What?

18:45.533 --> 18:46.349
Looks like they just hit
the Brookstone

18:46.351 --> 18:47.851
in West Hollywood.

18:47.853 --> 18:50.628
How long do you think it's gonna
take for us to get there?

18:50.705 --> 18:51.963
You know I'm a sucker
for modern gadgetry.

18:52.040 --> 18:53.114
Jazz.

18:53.191 --> 18:54.966
Hey.

18:55.043 --> 18:57.377
Hey.
Hey.

18:57.453 --> 19:00.213
Um, I owe you guys

19:00.289 --> 19:04.291
a really, really
big apology.

19:04.369 --> 19:06.536
Well, if you're talking
about reparations,

19:06.538 --> 19:07.479
you can just Cash App me.
[ Clicks tongue ]

19:07.555 --> 19:10.315
[ Both chuckle ]

19:10.392 --> 19:13.893
Um, you guys --
you guys were right.

19:13.970 --> 19:16.154
I was definitely raised
to see the world

19:16.231 --> 19:19.306
in a very specific way,

19:19.384 --> 19:22.327
and I'll never see the world
like you guys do.

19:22.404 --> 19:24.812
No matter how liberal
my environment

19:24.890 --> 19:28.892
or how expanded
my world view is...

19:28.894 --> 19:30.985
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

19:31.062 --> 19:32.820
...I'll always have
some sort of blinders on.

19:32.898 --> 19:36.174
And I'm really, really sorry.

19:36.251 --> 19:38.843
Well, we appreciate it.

19:38.920 --> 19:40.570
Mm-hmm.
And i-it's all good.

19:40.572 --> 19:42.572
You know we love you,

19:42.574 --> 19:45.258
but most importantly,
thank you for hearing us.

19:45.334 --> 19:47.352
Yeah.
Yeah.

19:47.429 --> 19:49.262
I love you guys.

19:49.338 --> 19:50.430
Oh, come here.

19:50.506 --> 19:53.266
[ Chuckles ]

19:53.342 --> 19:55.509
<i>  As the country</i>
<i>  finally saw its blind spot,</i>

19:55.587 --> 19:59.364
<i>  we were also forced</i>
<i>  to take notice of our own.</i>

19:59.441 --> 20:01.682
<i>  The only thing we could do</i>

20:01.760 --> 20:03.368
<i>  was move forward</i>
<i>  with our eyes open</i>

20:03.445 --> 20:08.022
<i>  in an effort to be better</i>
<i>  people to those around us</i>

20:08.099 --> 20:09.857
<i>  and hope that the rest</i>
<i>  of the country</i>

20:09.935 --> 20:11.525
<i>  would eventually do the same.</i>

20:16.624 --> 20:19.384
Wow. This was not
what I thought it was at all.

20:19.461 --> 20:24.538
Jazz: Mmm. This is everything
I thought it would be.

20:24.616 --> 20:27.617
<i>  [ Smooth jazz music</i>
<i>  playing quietly ]</i>

20:27.619 --> 20:30.303
What? I didn't loot this.
I'm just taking advantage

20:30.379 --> 20:33.064
of the homie's
five-finger discount.

20:33.141 --> 20:34.399
Oh, my God.

20:34.476 --> 20:36.734
Is somebody playing
soft jazz?

20:36.811 --> 20:38.552
[ Chuckles ]
Yes. I am.

20:38.630 --> 20:41.055
It's coming straight
from this coffee mug.

20:41.132 --> 20:42.574
It has a Bluetooth speaker
in it.

20:42.650 --> 20:44.892
Like I said...gadgetry.

20:44.970 --> 20:47.078
♪

20:47.155 --> 20:48.946
Hmm.

20:49.023 --> 20:51.665
Gadgetry.
